Interpreted expressions evaluated for edges rendering or for their associated tool only have access to the `self` element. This is often not enough: for reference-based edges the `self` only tells the tool the source element from which the reference starts, but not what the reference points to (in the case of mono-valued reference, `self` combined with the mapping can sometimes be enough to find the target, but that is not general enough).

The idea is to ass two new variables, which would be defined in every relevant context (in particular in tools, but also during the edge rendering when evaluating expressions for a single edge instance):
* `semanticEdgeSource`: the semantic element at the source/origin of the edge instance;
* `semanticEdgeTarget`: the semantic element at the destination/target of the edge instance;

