If someone wants to contribute to an existing extension point, it replaces the default value but
sometime we may want to add additional values instead. This should be configurable. To solve this
issue, SiriusWebApplication should have an optional prop named extensionRegistryMergeStrategy
with the following type :
```
interface ExtensionRegistryMergeStrategy { 

	mergeComponentExtensions(
		identifier: string, 
		existingValues:ComponentExtension<any>[], 
		newValues: ComponentExtension<any>[]): ComponentExtension<any>[];

	mergeDataExtensions(
		identifier: string, 
		existingValue: DataExtension<any>, 
		newValue: DataExtension<any>): DataExtension<any>;
}
```
This strategy should be given to ExtensionRegistry#addAll in order to let contributors decide how
they want to merge their own extension registries with the default one. By default,
SiriusWebApplication should provide one which would add component extensions and override
data extensions:
```
class DefaultExtensionRegistryMergeStrategy implements ExtensionRegistryMergeStrategy {
 
	public mergeComponentExtensions(identifier: string, existingValues: ComponentExtension<any>[], newValues: ComponentExtension<any>[]): ComponentExtension<any>[] 
	{
		return [...existingValues, ...newValues];
	}

public mergeDataExtensions(identifier: string, existingValue: DataExtension<any>, newValue: DataExtension<any>): DataExtension<any> 			 
	{
		return newValue;
	 }
}
