Since the split of the metadata, the GraphQL field `EditingContext#representations` does not return representation metadata for transient representations. Contrary to `EditingContext#representation`. In a way, it was bound to happen since internally in Sirius Web, the only transient representations we have share a special status (explorer, details, related elements, validation, representations, etc). They do not appear in the onboard area and cannot be opened in the main tabs so they are ignored by some data fetchers to only consider persisted ones.

We should instead support any representations and instead provide dedicated data fetchers for the onboard area of Sirius Web to ask specifically for persisted representations with a field dedicated to the onboard area like:

```
type EditingContext {
  onboardArea: OnboardArea!;
}

type OnboardArea {
 representations(representationIds: [ID!]) // only return specific representations
}
```

One could for example want to only consider some specific representations for the onboard area which may include transient ones. This features should be validated by including some transient representations on Papaya... I have some idea on this topic.

